{"title": "Convenient Terminal Illness", "content": "So something bad is about to happen; a nuclear weapon is about to go off, or an asteroid is about to impact the planet and the only way to avoid this is if someone stays behind and sacrifices themselves to stop it. But who will go? All of these characters are life long friends. There's no easy way to decide. Or is there? One of the characters has an Incurable Cough of Death and only a few months to live. He'll do it - after all, he's dying anyway, and in a far less dramatic and spectacular way.\n\nThis trope is about when a character gives their life for something based on the reasoning that they're going to die soon anyway. It's a favorite for when a writer wants to make a bittersweet ending less bitter.\n\nOccasionally, the doctor will burst in just a second too late to explain that he tested the wrong vial and the character isn't (wasn't) going to die. Oh well, it's too late now!\n\nAs a Death Trope, all Spoilers will be unmarked ahead. Beware.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ConvenientTerminalIllness", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FullmetalAlchemistTheConquerorOfShamballa", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/XMen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MadagascarEscape2Africa", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SpaceCowboys", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TommyLeeJones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GranTorino", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JoeVersusTheVolcano", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RepoTheGeneticOpera", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Red", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CrookedHouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ColdPursuit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GalaxyQuest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndTheHalfBloodPrince", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndTheDeathlyHallows", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDresdenFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DeathMasks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheWishsongOfSh